Instructions on converting packages to modern structure:

1. Get a copy of pkgshell (all directories)
set deimos=/net/savitri/d/deimos/
cd deimos$
!tar -xvf /d/phillips/tar_pkgshell

2. Move old package into src/
src should contain mkpkg, *.x, *.cl, *.h *.par

3. movefile src/*.keys lib/keys/
## (movefile src/doc/* doc/  ; !rmdir src/doc)

4. 
edit pkgxxxx.* mkpkg lib/mkpkg.inc lib/root*.hd lib/zzsetenv.def src/mkpkgxxxx
:1,$s/pkgxxxx/deimos/g
:1,$s/PKGXXXX/DEIMOS/g


5. 
!mv pkgxxxx.cl  deimos.cl
!mv pkgxxxx.hd  deimos.hd
!mv pkgxxxx.men deimos.men
!mv pkgxxxx.par deimos.par
!mv lib/rootpkgxxxx.hd lib/rootdeimos.hd



6.
edit deimos.cl
... to add task definitions
... virtually like original .cl, except for $src/, and zzsetenv, package lines
edit deimos.hd
... to add hlp, src info for each task
edit deimos.men
... to add one-line description of each task
edit deimos.par
... to edit date.


7. resolve mkpkg/mkpkgxxxx in src/

8.  do the mkpkg thing:
del src/libpkg.a,src/deimos.cl,src/x_deimos.o 
mkpkg arch
mkpkg sparc   ## ( mkpkg ssun   mkpkg alpha )
mkpkg -p deimos


## eg:
##  :1,$s/DEIMOS/DEIMOS/g
##  :1,$s/deimos/deimos/g
